I accidentaI release prevention program and the chemicaI-specific prevention steps are implemented, Royal Madera Vineyards has assigned overall responsibility for the PSM elements to a partner in the firm. The partner has the overall responsibility for the development, implementation, and integration of the PSM elements. 

Five-Year Accident History; 

Royal Madera Vineyards has not had any accidental releases from the ammonia-based refrigeration system that have resulted in deaths, injuries, or significant property damage onsite, or known offsite deaths, injuries, evacuations, sheltering in place, property damage, or environmental damage in the last five years. 

Emergency Response Program; 

Royal Madera Vineyards has established an emergency action plan and a chain of command to respond to emergencies and to notify emergency responders when there is a need for a response. However, an 

emergency response program does not need to be developed for the facility since Royal Madera Vineyards employees will not respond to accidental releases of ammonia, the facility is included in the com munity 

emergency response plan, and appropriate mechanisms are in place to notify emergency responders. 

Planned Changes to Improve Safety; 

Royal Madera Vineyards relies on the expertise of qualified ammonia refrigeration contractors to regularly evaluate the need for any changes to the refrigeration equipment and to improve safety. Currently, Royal Madera Vineyards does not have any changes planned to improve safety associated with the ammonia refrigeration system.



In conclusion; Royal Madera Vineyards considered "earthquakes" as an external event on the Process Hazard Analysis (PHA). The recommendation resulting from this is to have a licensed PE or company that specializes in Ammonia Refrigeration Systems conduct a Mechanical Integrity Audit every 3 years. Royal Madera has done so and has now adapted this recommendation into their safe work practices (SWP).
